<text>The Montana Senate is the upper house of the Montana Legislature, the state legislative branch of the U.S. state of Montana. The body is composed of 50 senators elected for four years. Half of the Senate is up for election every two years.

==Composition of the Senate==
:&quot;69th Legislature – 2025–2026&quot;

===Leaders===
The leaders of the Montana Senate include:
===Members of the Montana Senate===

Montana limits its State Senators to two four-year terms (8 years) in any 16-year period.

